text: The London cable car, officially the IFS Cloud Cable Car is a cable car link across the Thames River in London. It was opened on June 28th 2012, and was originally sponsored by Emirates Air until June 28th, 2022, where it became sponsored by the technology firm IFS. The line comprises a 0.62 mile journey that crosses the Thames from the Greenwich Peninsula to the Royal Victoria Dock. == References == Category:Transport in the London Borough of Newham Category:Transport in the Royal Borough of Greenwich Category:Pages using gadget WikiMiniAtlas Category:Coordinates on Wikidata
